Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Pop the @Linda McCartney Veggie Sausages{6} on another lightly oiled baking tray and set aside. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Trim the @Spring Onion{2} and thinly slice. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%g} on the fine side of your #grater{}. Drain and rinse the @Cannellini Beans{1%can}.

When the wedges have been cooking for ~{15%minutes}, remove from the oven, turn them and sprinkle the cheese and spring onions over. Pop back on the top shelf to cook until golden and crispy, ~{10-15%minutes}. At the same time, pop the veggie sausages on the middle shelf of the oven to cook until starting to crisp up, ~{16%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when piping hot.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. When hot, add the shallot and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @Tomato Passata{1}, @Water{100%ml} and @Vegetable Stock Powder{1}. Bring to the boil, reduce the heat slightly and simmer, stirring gently until the beans have thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

When the beans are cooked, taste and add @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Stir in the @BBQ Sauce{32%g}.

When everything is ready, re-heat your BBQ beans through if necessary and serve with the veggie sausages with the wedges on the side. Enjoy!